<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <meta name="description" content="Fictional demo for a premium desk lamp micro page using real Unsplash lamp photography, tactile product detail, beam proof, specifications, and direct launch contact.">
  <title>Lumo Desk Lamp Teaser — Micro Package Demo</title>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://websites.lucakosowski.com/demos/micro/lumo-desk-lamp-teaser/">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Lumo Desk Lamp Teaser — Micro Package Demo">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Fictional demo for a premium desk lamp micro page using real Unsplash lamp photography, tactile product detail, beam proof, specifications, and direct launch contact.">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://websites.lucakosowski.com/demos/micro/lumo-desk-lamp-teaser/">
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="Websites by Luca Kosowski">
  <link rel="icon" href="favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body id="top" data-package-tier="micro" data-design-signature="product-night-stage" data-design-archetype="micro-product-stage">
  <a class="wd-back-link" href="/#demos" aria-label="Back to Website Development">← Back to Website Development</a>
  <header class="lumo-header">
    <a class="lumo-brand" href="#top" aria-label="Lumo desk lamp teaser home">
      <span>Lumo</span>
      <small>studio task light</small>
    </a>
    <nav aria-label="Lumo sections">
      <a href="#object">Object</a>
      <a href="#beam">Beam</a>
      <a href="#specs">Specs</a>
      <a href="#materials">Materials</a>
      <a href="#launch">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="product-hero" id="object" aria-labelledby="lumo-title">
      <div class="launch-copy">
        <p class="lumo-kicker">Fictional demo · Micro product page</p>
        <h1 id="lumo-title">Quiet light for serious desks.</h1>
        <p>Lumo is staged as a premium task lamp, not a gadget scheme: one warm beam, one sculpted shade, one concise product story. Real Unsplash lamp photography anchors the page so the design feels tangible before the copy starts selling.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Launch contact options">
          <a class="quiet-link primary" href="mailto:launch@example.test">Request launch notes</a>
          <a class="quiet-link secondary" href="#specs">Review specifications</a>
        </div>
        <dl class="hero-ledger" aria-label="Hero product facts">
          <div><dt>Temperature</dt><dd>2700K</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Throw</dt><dd>42 cm task pool</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Finish</dt><dd>Graphite / brass</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <figure class="lamp-stage" aria-label="Photographic product stage for the Lumo desk lamp">
        <img class="lamp-photo" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507473885765-e6ed057f782c?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1400&q=84" alt="Black desk lamp casting a warm focused beam on a dark studio desk" width="1400" height="1750" loading="eager" decoding="async">
        <div class="beam-field" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="shade-aperture" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="product-silhouette" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <div class="stage-plaque" aria-label="Product highlights">
          <strong>2700K lens</strong>
          <span>18° shade memory</span>
          <span>machined base</span>
        </div>
        <figcaption>Illustrative Unsplash photography paired with original static HTML and CSS art direction.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="beam-proof" id="beam" aria-labelledby="beam-title">
      <div>
        <p class="lumo-kicker">Beam proof</p>
        <h2 id="beam-title">Let the light explain the product first.</h2>
        <p>The page borrows the visual-first product-teaser pattern from the reference library, then grounds it with restrained labels and a functional beam diagram instead of hype copy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="beam-board" aria-label="Static beam behavior diagram">
        <span>soft falloff</span>
        <span>paper edge</span>
        <span>42 cm pool</span>
        <span>warm lens</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="spec-rail" id="specs" aria-labelledby="spec-title">
      <div class="spec-intro">
        <p class="lumo-kicker">Specification rail</p>
        <h2 id="spec-title">Numbers with a visible reason.</h2>
        <p>Specs stay short and tactile, closer to a product card in a design shop than a speculative hardware pitch.</p>
      </div>
      <article>
        <span>Color temperature</span>
        <strong>2700K</strong>
        <p>Warm evening focus for reading, sketching, and desk repair without sterile blue cast.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>Shade memory</span>
        <strong>18°</strong>
        <p>A narrow adjustment range keeps the beam on the work surface instead of the room.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>Task pool</span>
        <strong>42cm</strong>
        <p>Enough reach for a notebook, keyboard, and small tools without washing out the desk.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="material-story" id="materials" aria-labelledby="materials-title">
      <div class="material-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="lumo-kicker">Material tray</p>
          <h2 id="materials-title">Graphite shell, brass hinge, frosted lens.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Premium product pages work when the details feel handled. The tray pairs photographic evidence, finish swatches, and terse material copy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="material-layout">
        <figure class="detail-photo">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1513506003901-1e6a229e2d15?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=84" alt="Warm desk lamp photographed in a calm interior setting" width="1200" height="900" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <figcaption>Warm light reference, used as a mood and finish cue for this fictional demo.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="material-grid">
          <article class="swatch graphite"><span></span><h3>Powder-coated graphite</h3><p>Matte aluminum keeps the profile quiet and furniture-grade.</p></article>
          <article class="swatch brass"><span></span><h3>Brass hinge note</h3><p>A single warm hardware accent adds tactility without becoming jewelry.</p></article>
          <article class="swatch lens"><span></span><h3>Frosted lens</h3><p>Diffused glass softens the source while preserving a readable edge.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="desk-vignettes" aria-labelledby="uses-title">
      <p class="lumo-kicker">Desk contexts</p>
      <h2 id="uses-title">Four scenes, no fake commerce layer.</h2>
      <div class="vignette-grid">
        <article><span>01</span><h3>Reading stack</h3><p>Warm pool across paper and margin notes.</p></article>
        <article><span>02</span><h3>Sketch pass</h3><p>Shade angle stays useful beside a moving hand.</p></article>
        <article><span>03</span><h3>Repair notes</h3><p>High contrast for screws, labels, and small parts.</p></article>
        <article><span>04</span><h3>Late desk work</h3><p>Dimmed glow that belongs in a home studio after hours.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="micro-proof" aria-labelledby="scope-title">
      <p class="lumo-kicker">Micro scope</p>
      <h2 id="scope-title">A teaser page, not a storefront.</h2>
      <p>This fictional demo includes one static page, favicon, robots.txt, responsive CSS, product copy, real Unsplash image references, and direct email contact. No form, client script, tracking, purchasing flow, inventory state, CMS editing, or server-side feature is included.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="launch-note" id="launch" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
      <p class="lumo-kicker">Launch contact</p>
      <h2 id="contact-title">Keep the close as restrained as the object.</h2>
      <a class="quiet-link large" href="mailto:launch@example.test">launch@example.test</a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Fictional demo for Website Development package examples. Static Micro page.</p>
    <a href="#top">Back to top</a>
    <a class="footer-back-to-web-development" href="/#demos">← Back to Website Development</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
